

An angel is a supernatural being in various religions and mythologies. In Abrahamic religions and Zoroastrianism, angels are often depicted as benevolent celestial beings who act as intermediaries between God or Heaven and humanity. Other roles of angels include protecting and guiding human beings, and carrying out God's tasks. Angels are often described as having wings and halos, and being of great beauty.

In the Bible, angels are mentioned many times. The Hebrew word mal'akh, translated as "angel" in English, literally means "messenger". Angels are often described as having many roles in the Bible, including protecting God's people and carrying out his commands. They are also seen as intermediaries between God and humans, and as messengers of God's word. In the New Testament, angels are seen as messengers of the gospel, and as protectors of the faithful.

In Islam, angels are seen as messengers of God, and as protectors of the faithful. The angels are seen as intermediaries between God and humans, and as helpers of humanity. Angels are also seen as bringing revelation from God to humanity. The Quran mentions several angels, such as Gabriel, Michael, and Israfil.

In Christianity, angels are seen as messengers of God, and as protectors of the faithful. Angels are often seen as intermediaries between God and humans, and as messengers of God's word. Angels are also seen as bringing revelation from God to humanity. The Bible mentions several angels, such as Gabriel, Michael, and Raphael.

In Judaism, angels are seen as messengers of God, and as protectors of the faithful. Angels are seen as intermediaries between God and humans, and as messengers of God's word. Angels are also seen as bringing revelation from God to humanity. The Bible mentions several angels, such as Gabriel, Michael, and Raphael.

In modern culture, angels are often seen as benevolent supernatural beings who act as intermediaries between God or Heaven and humanity. Angels are often seen as protectors of the faithful, and as messengers of God's word. In popular culture, angels are often depicted as having wings and halos, and being of great beauty.

In summary, angels are supernatural beings in various religions and mythologies. In Abrahamic religions and Zoroastrianism, angels are often seen as messengers of God, and as protectors of the faithful. Angels are often seen as intermediaries between God and humans, and as messengers of God's word. In popular culture, angels are often depicted as having wings and halos, and being of great beauty.